<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,466,979,1006]" box="[151,466,979,1006]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,466,979,1006]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,466,979,1006]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[151,382,980,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geodes">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,382,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Mesophleps geodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,1050,1765]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Labial palpus segment 2 broadly triangular, 3 upturned at right angles or porrect and obscured in 2. Forewing with moderate pterostigma basad of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[522,530,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[562,570,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">3</subScript>
approximated to common stalk of R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[982,1006,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">4+5</subScript>
+M 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1047,1055,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1093,1101,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1209,1217,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
connate or stalked; hind wing with R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[350,358,1140,1154]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
present, anastomosed with Sc near base of wing, Rs+M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[999,1007,1140,1154]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
on long common stalk, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1310,1318,1140,1154]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1428,1436,1140,1154]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
approximated at base. Forewing uniformly dark brown, unmarked, or grey with more or less distinct markings. Pregenital abdomen with TIV–VIII (in female TIV–VII) with very broad, medially indented band of microtrichia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[217,1354,229,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-93@12.[202,1389,214,1889]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Morphology of Mesophleps spp. 11. abdominal sternal support system of M. epiochra (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 664a, Sattler; 12. ovipositor of M. tephrastis-group, lateral view; 13. 'signum' of M. tephrastis (Meyrick), slide no. 30947; 14. SVIII of M. bifidella sp. nov. holotype, ♂, slide no. 463c, Sattler; 15. SVIII of M. gigantella sp. nov., paratype, ♂, slide no. 30934; 16. SVIII of M. geodes (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 30939." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Figs 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[193,267,1236,1260]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[198,1404,207,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-78@13.[179,1423,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Abdomens of Mesophleps spp. 17. M. safranella (Legrand), ♀, slide no. 30970; 18. M. epiochra (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 15833; 19. M. geodes (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 30939; 20. M. geodes (Meyrick), ♀, slide no. 30937; 21. M. catericta (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 30972; 22. M. tephrastis (Meyrick), ♀, slide no. 30947." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">19–20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
